In Kestrel City, three hands steer the same wheel. The **Civic Renewal Office** sells “efficiency” at City Hall—grants, permits, clean audits—while quietly laundering favors through temp contracts and sealed personnel files. The **Giltwake Syndicate** keeps the docks “orderly” with union muscle and security work, but runs missing people as commodities, trading identities to the highest bidder. Above them, the **Vellum Club** hosts charity galas and scholarship drives, yet curates blackmail ledgers and buries scandals in courtroom dust. Renewal needs Giltwake’s deniable enforcement; Giltwake fears Vellum’s ledgers. Vellum bankrolls Renewal, then demands silence—until someone like Silas starts pulling receipts.

